profile.primary_concern: navigating mental health alongside PrEP adherence

context: As a woman living with bipolar disorder, you face challenges in managing your mental health while considering PrEP. You worry that your mood swings might affect your ability to take the medication consistently, and there is a fear of stigma from both mental health and HIV perspectives. Despite these challenges, you hope to find a way to protect your health without compromising your mental stability.
